is it a good thing that i grew out of meowing out loud at my classmates?? yes bahaha but i also miss how passionately i did things. my love of art and the fandoms i enioyed and how much joy they brought me. all dropped so i could ✨fit in✨

when my innate love of learning wore off, my “giftedness” slipped away and i struggled to make the grades i used to. but none of this really even mattered until i dropped out of college and finally at age 20 got confirmation from professionals that yes, i am neurodivergent lmao

i didn’t let myself enjoy my interests or express myself because i didn’t want to be perceived as “weird”. things only started making sense when i considered how much i struggled with time management and getting schoolwork done

i picked up on a lot of my nd behaviors because i was able to pick up on how my peers thought i was weird and didn’t really accept me. by mid-late high school i was spending so much energy assimilating and regulating myself so that i’d appear “normal”
